<TITLE> McCain may share world stage with fellow oldsters </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Washington, Feb 22 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - John McCain would be the oldest first-term US president at age 72 if he wins the November election to succeed President George W. Bush. Here are the ages of some world leaders: - Robert Mugabe, president of Zimbabwe, 84. - Abdullah bin Abdul-Aziz al-Saud, king of Saudi Arabia, 83. - Islam Karimov, president of Uzbekistan, 70. - Hu Jintao, president of China, 65. - Raul Castro, positioned to soon replace his retired brother Fidel Castro as the leader of Cuba, 76. - Gordon Brown, prime minister of Britain, 57. - Felipe Calderon, president of Mexico, 45. - Stephen Harper, prime minister of Canada, 48.
